article.headline: Colorado State 79, Stetson 70
article.story: DELAND, Fla. (AP) -- Reserve center Matt Nelson scored 25 points, helping Colorado State defeat Stetson 79-70 on Saturday night. Nelson was 6-of-8 from the floor and made all 13 of his free throws, breaking the 20-point mark for the 20th time in his college career. E.J. Gordon scored 27 of his career-high 31 points in the second half for Stetson, which allowed Colorado State to shoot 52.3 percent from the floor and was outrebounded 41-27. Gordon had team-highs of seven rebounds and six steals, while shooting 11-of-28 from the field. Colorado State (5-4), which snapped a two-game losing streak, controlled much of the game, eventually building an 18-point lead with 1:13 left. Stetson outscored the Rams 12-3 in the final 62 seconds. Matt Williams had 14 points and eight rebounds, while Ronnie Clark had nine points and 13 rebounds for Colorado State. Kevin Craig had 10 points for Stetson (2-4), which has lost all four of its games against Division I opponents this season.
